API Gateway (Deep Dive):
  A single entry point for all client requests in a microservices architecture.
  👉 Instead of:
        Client → Service A
        Client → Service B
        Client → Service C
  👉 You use: Client → API Gateway → Services
  Responsibilities:
        🔐 Authentication & Authorization (JWT validation)
        🚦 Routing requests to services
        📊 Rate limiting
        🧾 Logging & monitoring
        🔄 Load balancing

Flow with JWT:
    1. Client → /login → Auth Service → JWT
    2. Client → API Gateway (JWT in header)
    3. Gateway:
       → Validate JWT
       → Extract user info
       → Forward request
    4. Microservice:
       → Trust request (no re-authentication)

