Refresh Token Flow (VERY IMPORTANT)
🧩 Problem - JWT expires quickly (security)
👉 What happens after expiry?
    ✅ Solution: Refresh Token
      You issue 2 tokens:
      Token	            Purpose      	Expiry
      Access Token	    API access	  Short (15 min)
      Refresh Token	    Get new token	Long (7 days)

1. Login: → Access Token + Refresh Token
2. API calls: → Use Access Token
3. If expired:→ Send Refresh Token
4. Server:→ Validate Refresh Token  → Issue new Access Token

    @PostMapping("/refresh")
    public String refresh(@RequestBody String refreshToken) {
        if (isValid(refreshToken)) {
            return generateNewAccessToken();
        }
        throw new RuntimeException("Invalid refresh token");
    }

Best Practices:
      Store refresh token in DB
      Use HttpOnly cookies
      Rotate refresh tokens (important 🔥)
⚠️ Common Mistakes:
      ❌ Storing refresh token in localStorage
      ❌ Not expiring refresh tokens
      ❌ No rotation → security risk


OAuth2 + JWT Combined Architecture:
🧩 Why Combine? OAuth2 → Login (Google, Okta) and JWT → Internal API security
 Flow:
    1. User → Login with Google
    2. Google → returns user info
    3. Backend: → Generate JWT (own token)
    4. Client:  → Use JWT for API calls
    👉 OAuth2 is external authentication
    👉 JWT is internal authorization

Spring Boot Flow:
    Step 1: OAuth2 Login http.oauth2Login();
    Step 2: Success Handler
        @Component
        public class OAuthSuccessHandler implements AuthenticationSuccessHandler {

            @Override
            public void onAuthenticationSuccess(HttpServletRequest request,
                                                HttpServletResponse response,
                                                Authentication authentication) {
                String username = authentication.getName();
                String jwt = generateToken(username);
                response.getWriter().write(jwt);
            }
        }
    Step 3: Use JWT for APIs
            Frontend → sends JWT → Gateway → Services

